If you are a doctor I would not advise you to hire a doctorate from the tiny regional hospital. They will just tell you to Google it. Who are you going to ask, anyway?

-How are your Spanish-speaking skills?

Most people speak in Quichua. Hand gestures used by United States kids in the ‘80’s have been replaced. Since Spanish is so proactive, some households will adopt three or four languages.

-Could the community use anything that you can bring?

Children in Ecuador are poor. Please ask Murrieta Marketing talk to their clients and find out exactly what the children are needing in EACH of the towns Murrieta Marketing will be visiting. Bring them all you can and have money taken out of each check for a fund to buy more while in Ecuador.

-Can you speak to children in the most isolated communities known as the parto escuela?

Many communities are just that – communities – really small kids, moms and dads. When meeting families for the first time, it would be a good idea to speak with them in Spanish. This cannot be stressed enough.
